    <p class="section-number">05, Real repair stories</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Recent gas fireplace jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Pacific Palisades, Heat &amp; Glo SL-550TR direct-vent, 14 years old</h3>
        <p>Won't stay lit. Thermocouple test: 12 mV (needs 18+ mV for valve to hold). Replaced thermocouple AND pilot generator together, they age together, and replacing one and not the other is a callback in 6 months. Tested pilot stable, main burner ignition, remote pairing.</p>
        <p><strong>Total: $385.</strong></p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Beverly Hills, Valor LX2 direct-vent, 2018 install</h3>
        <p>Pilot lights, won't fire main burner. Tested gas valve solenoid: open circuit. Replaced valve assembly (Valor proprietary, 4-day order).</p>
        <p><strong>Total: $120 diagnostic first visit + $580 part + $180 labor on second visit = $880.</strong> Owner appreciated honest scope: this would've been double at most service shops.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Calabasas, Heatilator Constitution-50, 2015 install</h3>
        <p>Remote handheld working, fireplace won't fire. Diagnosed: receiver battery dead inside the firebox housing. Most owners don't know there's a battery in the receiver. Replaced battery ($8 retail), tested. Working.</p>
        <p><strong>Total: $120 diagnostic only</strong>, felt wrong to charge labor on a battery swap. Customer asked for our card.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Brentwood, outdoor Hearth Products Controls valve, 7 years old</h3>
        <p>Outdoor fire pit not igniting. Pilot orifice clogged with web (literally). Cleaned, tested, working.</p>
        <p><strong>Total: $120 visit + 15 minutes = $120.</strong> Customer gave us a $50 tip and said his last contractor wanted $400 to "rebuild the system."</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Newport Beach, Majestic outdoor linear fireplace, 2020 install</h3>
        <p>Won't ignite. Multiple component failures from salt air corrosion at 4-5 years (way premature for inland install, Newport coastal exposure does this). Replaced ignition module + thermopile.</p>
        <p><strong>Total: $620.</strong></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

